{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3d8e2711-ec23-4f82-87bc-5dbd36531ac6","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **Hot-reload** on every code change (`dotnet watch`)\n- **Filter** to only that single test via `--filter`\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so it matches without needing the full namespace. You can also use an exact match:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName=Contoso.Payments.Tests.PaymentProcessorTests.ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"358ee5bb-f4b4-4fde-9173-299afc0b186b","outputTokens":166,"requestId":"7C19:175BE3:28AE67E:2D2683C:69F94BA5"},"id":"802aff19-c576-44ab-8e5f-ac48805d56c1","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:45:14.582Z","parentId":"47c95a9a-a217-423c-a67b-ff55ee4e0f26"}
